criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Unformed Stool specimens from patients suspected of having CDI for whom diagnostic
             tests are indicated and ordered;

          -  At least 1.25mL of unformed stool specimen (defined as specimen assuming the shape of
             its container);

          -  Only one (1) specimen per patient will be included in the study;

          -  Materials use within their expiration date;

          -  Transport, storage times, and conditions (e.g. room temperature and/or refrigerated)
             within requested indications.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Specimens from patients for whom CDI diagnostic tests have not been ordered;

          -  Transport and storage times and conditions that exceed these Study Protocol
             requirements;

          -  Formed or hard stool specimens or rectal swabs.
